column3: My Sunday riding buddy has a Zullo, beautiful frame and a wild paint job. It's the yellow/brown sand wavy one, the Tour 91 frameset. He bought it right from Zullo at the NAHBS a few years ago. Zullo didn't want to have to bring it back through customs, so gave him an awesome deal. It's a lovely bike!
"Essere una lumaca che lascia una traccia e non una lepre che corre senza lasciare nemmeno un'impronta", notevole.
no matter how hard it can be, you never know before you try.
I want to make films with you Rapha!
